messages.subject: Growing Up - Moving to California
messages.msgSnippet: Renee:  I ve had to do the same thing with my mother.  She s has constantly stuck her nose in and decided what s best for my life and the life of my children
messages.messageBody:
Renee: I've had to do the same thing with my mother. She's has constantly
stuck her nose in and decided what's best for my life and the life of my
children and doesn't "approve" of homeschooling (much less unschooling)...
Hubby and I, over this weekend, have decided NOT to move to the new house we
are having built in Tucson/Vail. We are going to move directly to Northern
California by August of this year and get where we actually want to
go....Those of you living in Northern California.... it would be great if
you would e-mail me privately and let me know more about your area. We need
all the support you guys have to give to do this giant move, and yet we know
it's the best thing for us.

Dawn

messages.messageBody:
I got this from another list:

Subject: TOMS ART CONTEST

FROM PAT W (MHL):
I've had this paper for a long time, and haven't had a
chance to post
it.

Tom's of Maine has an art contest. Here's the message
on the
toothpaste
insert:

"River Stories" Video Art Contest
Create an original piece of artwork represetning your
favorite
river...That
special place you have that helps you connect to the
natural world, and
you
will be entered for a chance to win a FREE copy of the
Tom's of Maine
video,
"River Stories," a beautifully filmed tale of three
at-risk rivers, the
Rio
Grande, the St. John and the Chattahoochee. You will
learn about the
conservation, restoration, and stewardship efforts on
these rivers'
behalf.

Send your art to:
River Art Contest
c/o Tom's of Maine
P.O. Box 710
Kennebunk, ME 04043

Note: Entry deadline for art contest is March 31,
2002. 15 winners
will be
chosen and will be notified in June, 2002.
